# ─── Server ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PORT=3000
HOST=0.0.0.0
NODE_ENV=development
LOG_LEVEL=info

# ─── Firebase Admin ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to service account key JSON (local dev only — use Workload Identity in GCP)
GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=./service-account.dev.json
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=teranga-events-dev
FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=teranga-events-dev.appspot.com

# ─── CORS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3001,http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:3002

# ─── Rate Limiting ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=100
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_MS=60000

# ─── Email (Resend) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RESEND_API_KEY=re_xxxx
RESEND_FROM_NAME=Teranga Events

# Legacy single-sender — kept as a fallback when a category var is unset.
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=events@terangaevent.com

# Per-category senders. Each EmailCategory resolves to one of these via the
# sender registry (apps/api/src/services/email/sender.registry.ts).
#   auth, transactional  → RESEND_FROM_EVENTS
#   organizational       → RESEND_FROM_HELLO
#   billing              → RESEND_FROM_BILLING
#   marketing            → RESEND_FROM_NEWS
#
# Don't use no-reply@: Resend's deliverability analyzer and the
# Gmail/Yahoo/Microsoft bulk-sender rules flag no-reply senders. We send
# from real, addressable mailboxes with Reply-To to support@.
RESEND_FROM_EVENTS=events@terangaevent.com
RESEND_FROM_HELLO=hello@terangaevent.com
RESEND_FROM_BILLING=billing@terangaevent.com
RESEND_FROM_NEWS=news@terangaevent.com

# Reply-To addresses. Must be real inboxes — Resend is outbound-only and will
# not receive replies. Point MX records at Google Workspace / Fastmail / etc.
RESEND_REPLY_TO_SUPPORT=support@terangaevent.com
RESEND_REPLY_TO_BILLING=billing@terangaevent.com
RESEND_REPLY_TO_CONTACT=contact@terangaevent.com

# Segment for marketing broadcasts (Resend's current term; formerly
# "Audience"). Create in the Resend dashboard (Segments → New segment)
# and paste the id below. When unset the newsletter path is dormant —
# subscribe still records the email in Firestore, but sendNewsletter
# no-ops instead of erroring.
# RESEND_NEWSLETTER_SEGMENT_ID=seg_...

# ─── SMS (Africa's Talking) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
AT_API_KEY=xxxx
AT_USERNAME=sandbox
AT_SENDER_ID=Teranga

# ─── QR Code Signing Secret ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Distinct placeholder from the other HMAC secrets below so a developer
# who copies this file verbatim does NOT end up with the same value
# across cryptographic domains. See comments on each secret for why
# domain separation matters.
QR_SECRET=change-me-QR-signing-secret-must-be-at-least-32-chars
# QR_MASTER is required for v4 HKDF per-event key derivation (offline sync).
# Must be at least 32 chars and different from QR_SECRET.
# QR_MASTER=change-this-to-a-different-strong-secret-min-32-chars

# ─── Webhook ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
WEBHOOK_SECRET=change-this-to-a-strong-secret-min-16-chars

# ─── Observability ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sentry DSN for error tracking (optional — leave empty for local dev)
# SENTRY_DSN=https://examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0

# ─── Payment Providers ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PAYMENT_WEBHOOK_SECRET=strong-secret-for-payment-webhooks
# WAVE_API_KEY=
# WAVE_API_SECRET=
# ORANGE_MONEY_API_URL=https://api.orange.com/orange-money-webpay/dev/v1
# ORANGE_MONEY_CLIENT_ID=
# ORANGE_MONEY_CLIENT_SECRET=
# ORANGE_MONEY_MERCHANT_KEY=
# PLATFORM_FEE_RATE=0.05

# ─── Public URLs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# All absolute URLs the API emits into emails or hands to payment providers
# are built from these three, via apps/api/src/config/public-urls.ts. When
# the domain changes, update these env vars (or the Cloud Run env config) —
# no source code changes needed.
#
# Defaults ship to localhost so `npm run api:dev` works without .env setup.
# Staging/production MUST override all three to the real public hosts.
API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
PARTICIPANT_WEB_URL=http://localhost:3002
WEB_BACKOFFICE_URL=http://localhost:3001

# ─── Newsletter Double Opt-In ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HMAC secret for stateless newsletter confirmation tokens. Separate from
# QR_SECRET so the two cryptographic domains can't compromise each other.
# Min 32 chars. Rotate by generating a new value — pending tokens signed
# with the old secret will fail verification and users will need to
# re-subscribe (acceptable because tokens expire in 7 days anyway).
NEWSLETTER_CONFIRM_SECRET=change-me-newsletter-confirm-secret-min-32-chars

# ─── Unsubscribe Links (non-mandatory email) ─────────────────────────────────
# HMAC secret for the List-Unsubscribe tokens embedded in transactional /
# organizational emails. Tokens do NOT expire so users can click an email
# from months ago and still unsubscribe.
#
# ROTATION RUNBOOK
# Rotating this secret simultaneously invalidates every outstanding
# unsubscribe link in every historical email we ever sent. Users with
# no Teranga account (newsletter-only subscribers) lose their one-click
# unsubscribe path and must either re-subscribe + re-confirm to opt out,
# or use Resend's Segment-level unsubscribe (for marketing broadcasts).
#
# Before rotating in prod:
#   1. Announce via the transactional channel (notify every active
#      subscriber that links in old emails are about to expire).
#   2. Wait at least 72h so Gmail / Apple Mail's cached one-click POST
#      attempts drain.
#   3. Rotate via `firebase functions:secrets:set UNSUBSCRIBE_SECRET`.
#   4. Monitor the next-day bounce + complaint rates as a sanity check.
#
# A future enhancement would be to verify against BOTH the previous and
# current secret during a grace window — tracked as a follow-up.
UNSUBSCRIBE_SECRET=change-me-unsubscribe-secret-min-32-chars

# ─── API Keys (T2.3) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HMAC secret used to derive the 4-char checksum stamped on every
# plaintext `terk_<env>_<body>_<checksum>` API key. The checksum lets
# the auth middleware reject typo'd / corrupted keys BEFORE a Firestore
# read. Compromising this secret does NOT let an attacker forge valid
# keys — authentication compares SHA-256(key) against the stored hash;
# the checksum is purely a transport-layer integrity check.
#
# Separate from QR_SECRET / NEWSLETTER_CONFIRM_SECRET / UNSUBSCRIBE_SECRET
# so a compromise of one cryptographic domain cannot leak the others.
# Min 32 chars.
#
# ROTATION RUNBOOK — BLAST RADIUS
# Rotating this secret invalidates the checksum on EVERY outstanding
# API key across EVERY org. Effect: `parseApiKey()` returns null in the
# middleware → every request authenticated with a pre-rotation key gets
# a 401. This is equivalent to a platform-wide bulk-revoke.
#
# Rotation is a compliance + support event. Do NOT rotate without:
#   1. An incident ticket explaining why (e.g. secret was leaked).
#   2. Customer communication at least 48h in advance — enterprise
#      integrations will need to re-issue every key.
#   3. A Super-Admin-authored announcement via /admin/announcements
#      with `severity: critical` published before the rotation.
#
# For routine secret rotation, DO NOT rotate this — instead, have
# customers rotate their individual keys via /organization/api-keys.
API_KEY_CHECKSUM_SECRET=change-me-api-key-checksum-secret-min-32-chars

# Emergency kill-switch. When `true`, the auth middleware rejects every
# `terk_*` bearer token with a 401 so API-key auth is effectively
# disabled platform-wide without a code deploy. Flip this via Cloud
# Run env-var edit if the `apiKeys` collection is degraded or an
# incident requires an emergency freeze. Regular Firebase-ID-token
# auth is unaffected.
# API_KEY_AUTH_DISABLED=false
